{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"id52ddee1f-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6","identifier":"/us/usc/t28/s2402"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2402"},"text":"§ 2402.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Jury trial in actions against United States","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subject to chapter 179 of this title, any action against the United States under section 1346 shall be tried by the court without a jury, except that any action against the United States under section 1346(a)(1) shall, at the request of either party to such action, be tried by the court with a jury.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"id52ddee20-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646"},"text":"June 25, 1948, ch. 646","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/971"},"text":"62 Stat. 971","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1954-07-30/ch648/s2/a"},"text":"July 30, 1954, ch. 648, § 2(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/68/589"},"text":"68 Stat. 589","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/331/s3/b/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–331, § 3(b)(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-10-26"},"text":"Oct. 26, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/4069"},"text":"110 Stat. 4069","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"id52ddee21-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"id52ddee22-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., §§ 41(20), 931(a) (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s24"},"text":"Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 24","children":[],"tail":", par. 20, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/36/1093"},"text":"36 Stat. 1093","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1921-11-23/ch136/s1310/c"},"text":"Nov. 23, 1921, ch. 136, § 1310(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/311"},"text":"42 Stat. 311","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1924-06-02"},"text":"June 2, 1924","children":[],"tail":", 4:01 p.m., ch. 234, § 1025(c), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/348"},"text":"43 Stat. 348","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1925-02-24/ch309"},"text":"Feb. 24, 1925, ch. 309","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/43/972"},"text":"43 Stat. 972","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1926-02-26/ch27"},"text":"Feb. 26, 1926, ch. 27","children":[],"tail":", §§ 1122(c), 1200, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/44/121"},"text":"44 Stat. 121","children":[],"tail":", 125; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1946-08-02/ch753/s410/a"},"text":"Aug. 2, 1946, ch. 753, § 410(a)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/60/843"},"text":"60 Stat. 843","children":[],"tail":")."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section consolidates non-jury provisions of sections 41(20) and 931(a) of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed. For other provisions of said section 931(a) relating to tort claims, see Distribution Table.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Word “actions” was substituted for “suits”, in view of Rule 2 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Provisions of title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 41(20) relating to jurisdiction of district courts and time for bringing actions against the United States are the basis of sections 1346 and 2401 of this title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"id52ddee23-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id52ddee24-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/331"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–331","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Subject to chapter 179 of this title, any action” for “Any action”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1954—Act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1954-07-30"},"text":"July 30, 1954","children":[],"tail":", permitted a jury trial at the request of either party in actions under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t28/s1346/a/1"},"text":"section 1346(a)(1) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id52ddee25-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id52ddee26-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1996 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/331"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–331","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"199